# Exponential and S-curve shapes: SPEC-GAP. The manual says these are only "tuned
# to sound similar" to linear with NO stated time constant, so exact curves need
# a hardware/reference trace. We implement exponential as a one-pole low-pass
# (tau = effective slew) and S-curve as two cascaded one-poles (S-shaped step
# response). Here we assert only the shape-independent invariants: both are
# gradual (not instant) at the first tick and both converge to the target.
# slew=0.05, input stepped to 0.05, tickrate 100. Linear (exact) reaches 0.05 in
# 3 ticks (step 0.02/tick); exp/scurve converge within tol by tick 99.
tickrate 100
patch <<<
[slew]
    input       = I1
    slew        = 0.05
    exponential = O1
    linear      = O2
    scurve      = O3
>>>
@0 set I1 0.05
# linear is limited to 0.02 on the first tick (exact)
@0 expect O2 0.02 tol 1e-6
# all three have converged to the target by tick 99
@99 expect O1 0.05 tol 1e-3
@99 expect O2 0.05 tol 1e-6
@99 expect O3 0.05 tol 1e-3
